Use citrus peels of any kind to freshen up that smelly garbage disposal. All you have to do is cut up the peel and put it in the disposal. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/88/Use-Citrus-Fruit-Peels-in-the-Home-and-Garden-Step-7Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Use-Citrus-Fruit-Peels-in-the-Home-and-Garden-Step-7Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/88/Use-Citrus-Fruit-Peels-in-the-Home-and-Garden-Step-7Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Use-Citrus-Fruit-Peels-in-the-Home-and-Garden-Step-7Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
